Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, possibly akrater or dinos; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between reddish brown margins, with numerous mica inclusions; slip almost completely worn and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: From the same vessel as 1965, 0930.414 and perhaps 1888,0601.618.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.091)
